Note: ============================================================================
Note: DELETE -- public
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Public delete. Removes the key (and its value) from the tree if
present and returns 1; returns 0 if the key was absent or the tree
handle is invalid.

The descent is iterative and follows the CLRS B-tree-delete invariant:
before stepping into any child, the current node x guarantees that
that child has at least t keys. This way the child can absorb a key
loss without violating the minimum-keys property. When a leaf is
reached we simply remove the key in O(t) by shifting.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Loop on current node `cur` starting from the root:
1) Linear-scan for the smallest index i with cur.keys[i] >= key.
2) If found at i and cur is a leaf: shift remove and decrement size,
   return 1. (Leaf rooted at the original root case: root may end up
   empty, but the empty leaf root is allowed.)
3) If found at i and cur is internal:
   a) If children[i] has >= t keys: take predecessor (k', v') from
      children[i], copy into cur.keys[i]/values[i], then continue
      delete with key = k' descending into children[i].
   b) Else if children[i+1] has >= t keys: take successor (k', v')
      from children[i+1], copy into cur.keys[i]/values[i], then
      continue delete with key = k' descending into children[i+1].
   c) Else merge children[i] and children[i+1] (which both have
      exactly t-1 keys) along with cur.keys[i] into children[i]
      (which then has 2t-1 keys). cur loses one key. Continue with
      cur = children[i].
4) If not found: if cur is a leaf, the key is absent -> return 0.
   Otherwise determine the child slot idx to descend into, ensure
   that child has >= t keys via btree_ensure_child_has_t (which
   handles borrows and merges and may adjust idx), and descend.

After 3c, if cur == root and root.kc == 0, the merge collapsed the
root and the surviving children[0] becomes the new root. We patch the
tree header and free the old root.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(t log n). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if the key was absent or the tree handle was 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "btree_delete" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If cur is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let active_key be key
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let kc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        Let is_leaf be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
        Note: Locate first index i with keys[i] >= active_key, or kc.
        Let i be 0
        Let found_at be 0 minus 1
        While i is less than kc:
            Let k_addr be proc btree_key_addr with cur, i
            Let k be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with k_addr, 0
            If active_key is equal to k:
                Set found_at to i
                Set i to kc
            Otherwise:
                If active_key is less than k:
                    Set i to kc
                Otherwise:
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End While
        Note: i is now either found_at marker is set, or i = kc means
        Note: descend into rightmost child, else i is the descent slot.
        If found_at is greater than or equal to 0:
            If is_leaf is equal to 1:
                Note: leaf removal: shift left.
                Let j be found_at
                While j is less than kc minus 1:
                    Let src_k be proc btree_key_addr with cur, j plus 1
                    Let dst_k be proc btree_key_addr with cur, j
                    Let src_v be proc btree_value_addr with cur, j plus 1
                    Let dst_v be proc btree_value_addr with cur, j
                    Let kv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src_k, 0
                    Let vv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src_v, 0
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with dst_k, 0, kv
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with dst_v, 0, vv
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 0, kc minus 1
                Let sz be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, sz minus 1
                Return 1
            End If
            Note: internal node case: try predecessor / successor / merge
            Let left_c_addr be proc btree_child_addr with cur, found_at
            Let left_child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with left_c_addr, 0
            Let left_child_kc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with left_child, 0
            Let right_c_addr be proc btree_child_addr with cur, found_at plus 1
            Let right_child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with right_c_addr, 0
            Let right_child_kc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with right_child, 0
            If left_child_kc is greater than or equal to BTREE_ORDER:
                Let pk be proc btree_predecessor_key with left_child
                Let pv be proc btree_predecessor_value with left_child
                Let dst_k be proc btree_key_addr with cur, found_at
                Let dst_v be proc btree_value_addr with cur, found_at
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with dst_k, 0, pk
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with dst_v, 0, pv
                Set active_key to pk
                Set cur to left_child
            Otherwise:
                If right_child_kc is greater than or equal to BTREE_ORDER:
                    Let sk be proc btree_successor_key with right_child
                    Let sv be proc btree_successor_value with right_child
                    Let dst_k be proc btree_key_addr with cur, found_at
                    Let dst_v be proc btree_value_addr with cur, found_at
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with dst_k, 0, sk
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with dst_v, 0, sv
                    Set active_key to sk
                    Set cur to right_child
                Otherwise:
                    Note: merge left_child + sep + right_child into left_child
                    proc btree_merge_children with cur, found_at
                    Note: if cur is root and now empty, collapse.
                    Let cur_kc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
                    Let root_check be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
                    If cur_kc is equal to 0 and cur is equal to root_check:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, left_child
                        proc deallocate from Layout with cur
                    End If
                    Set cur to left_child
                End If
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If is_leaf is equal to 1:
                Note: key not in tree
                Return 0
            End If
            Note: determine descent index: smallest index where keys[idx] > active_key, or kc
            Let idx be 0
            Let scan be 0
            Let scan_done be 0
            While scan is less than kc:
                If scan_done is equal to 0:
                    Let k_addr be proc btree_key_addr with cur, scan
                    Let k be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with k_addr, 0
                    If active_key is less than k:
                        Set idx to scan
                        Set scan_done to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set idx to scan plus 1
                    End If
                End If
                Set scan to scan plus 1
            End While
            Note: ensure children[idx] has >= t keys before descending.
            Let new_idx be proc btree_ensure_child_has_t with cur, idx
            Note: ensure may have collapsed root.
            Let cur_kc2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
            Let root_check2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
            If cur_kc2 is equal to 0 and cur is equal to root_check2:
                Let only_child_addr be proc btree_child_addr with cur, 0
                Let only_child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with only_child_addr, 0
                If only_child is not equal to 0:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, only_child
                    proc deallocate from Layout with cur
                    Set cur to only_child
                Otherwise:
                    Let c_addr be proc btree_child_addr with cur, new_idx
                    Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Let c_addr be proc btree_child_addr with cur, new_idx
                Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process
